### Having diabetes doesn't mean you need to stop eating your favourite food.
Most meals – particularly old favourites – can be tweaked so that they're
healthier, but you don't lose out on any of that great flavour.
Each dish has a healthy recipe and a demo video to show you how you can cook
them for yourself at home. Give them a go!
* How to cook: fish and chips \- Delicious and healthier fish and chips, made from scratch, complete with mushy peas. 
* How to cook: apple crumble \- A traditional, tasty dessert, with a healthy twist.A traditional, tasty dessert, with a healthy twist. 
* How to cook: ham and leek frittata \- Learn to make a delicious cooked breakfast for one. 
* How to cook: make-ahead mince \- See how to make a big batch of mince ahead of time, which you can freeze and use up in lots of different dishes. 
* How to cook: Thai chicken stir fry \- Find out how to cook your own stir fry in minutes, which makes a perfect quick mid-week meal.
